etdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Mondraker-MIND-integrated-telemetry-tracking-suspension-setup-and-analysis_2021-Mondraker-Crafty-Carbon-Mind-enduro-eMTB-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Mondraker-MIND-integrated-telemetry-tracking-suspension-setup-and-analysis_2021-Mondraker-Crafty-Carbon-Mind-enduro-eMTB-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Mondraker-MIND-integrated-telemetry-tracking-suspension-setup-and-analysis_2021-Mondraker-Crafty-Carbon-Mind-enduro-eMTB-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-251209\">2021 Mondraker Crafty Carbon MIND eMTB</figcaption></figure><p>And for now the bike with Mind suspension telemetry systems are exclusive to Europe (incl. UK &amp; CH). <em>The Mind system adds about 300€ to the standard bike price. That means the Foxy Carbon R with MIND will be the lowest-priced enduro bike at 5300€, or the lowest-priced Craft Carbon R eMTB at 7800€ (representative euro pricing, individual countries will vary a bit).&nbsp;</em></p><p>Mondraker does say they plan to bring Mind setups to more XC, Trail, Enduro &amp; DH mountain bikes as soon as possible over “the next few years”, so hopefully that will expand worldwide quickly, as well. Mondraker CEO Miguel Pina says he’s excited by the idea that “everyone who rides a Mondraker will from now on be able to enjoy the benefits of a properly set up bike.”</p><p><em>It is less geared toward racers, and more about getting regular recreation mountain bikers to have a better sense of how their suspension performs</em>. As a tech-loving mountain biker who knows how finicky suspension setup can be for anyone, I think that sounds like an excellent goal.</p><p><a href=\"https://mondraker.com/wo/en/mind\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Mondraker.com/MIND</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor"